      • getSource

      • getSink

        IVertex getSink()

      • getSource

        IVertex getSource(IVertex assumed_sink)
        This method is only meaningful in an undirected context, where it will return the source vertex given that the caller has passed in what they are treating as the sink vertex. In a directed context this is equivalent to getSource(). If the context is unknown it is recommended to use this method instead of getSource().
        Parameters:
        assumed_sink - the vertex the caller is treating as the sink
        Returns:
        the source vertex given the assumed sink

      • getSink

        IVertex getSink(IVertex assumed_source)
        This method is only meaningful in an undirected context, where it will return the sink vertex given that the caller has passed in what they are treating as the source vertex. In a directed context this is equivalent to getSink(). If the context is unknown it is recommended to use this method instead of getSink().
        Parameters:
        assumed_source - the vertex the caller is treating as the source
        Returns:
        the sink vertex given the assumed source
